<h1>L'area</h1>
<h2>The Area</h2>
<p>The villa is in the countryside between the towns of Vicchio and Borgo San Lorenzo in northeast Tuscany. Vicchio's small downtown features local restaurants and shops and there are a variety of attractions in the area.</p>
<p>The town of Vicchio is the birthplace of Giotto, the famous 14th century painter and architect. Among his numerous works are the bell tower of the Duomo in Florence, the frescoes of the Scrovegni Chapel in Padua, the Basilica inferiore in Assisi, the Bardi and Peruzzi Chapels in Florence.</p>
<p>Within an hour, there are vineyards, a golf course and a famous Formula 1 race track. More information about regional attractions coming soon.</p>

<h1>Trasporti</h1>
<h2>Transportation</h2>
<h3>Step 1: Getting to Florence</h3>
<p>Vicchio is 40 KM northeast of Florence, so getting to Florence is step one.</p>
<p>You can fly directly into Florence, but may find better fares into other places such as Rome, Venice or Milan. All three of those locations are only about 2 hours from Florence by train.</p>
<p>Unlike in the US, trains are fast, affordable and easy to use in Italy. We won't list all the information about trains here (a little is below), just know that wherever you can find the best flight, it's probably just an easy train ride away from Florence.</p>
<p><b>When you book your flight, let us know where you are arriving and we can give you more detailed advice on buying train tickets.</b></p>
<p>There are pass options that will give you more flexibility to travel before or after the wedding as well as single ticket options.</p>

